type.name: org.gradle.plugins.ide.idea.model.Module
type.description: Represents the customizable elements of an iml (via XML hooks everything of the iml is customizable).

method.name: getContentPath
method.description: The directory for the content root of the module. Defaults to the project directory. If null, the directory containing the output file will be used.

method.name: getDependencies
method.description: The dependencies of this module. Must not be null.

method.name: getExcludeFolders
method.description: The directories to be excluded. Must not be null.

method.name: getGeneratedSourceFolders
method.description: The directories containing generated the production sources. Must not be null.

method.name: getOutputDir
method.description: The output directory for production classes. If null, no entry will be created.

method.name: getSourceFolders
method.description: The directories containing the production sources. Must not be null.

method.name: getTestOutputDir
method.description: The output directory for test classes. If null, no entry will be created.

method.name: getTestSourceFolders
method.description: The directories containing the test sources. Must not be null.

method.name: isInheritOutputDirs
method.description: If true, output directories for this module will be located below the output directory for the project; otherwise, #outputDir and #testOutputDir will take effect.

property.name: contentPath
property.description: The directory for the content root of the module. Defaults to the project directory. If null, the directory containing the output file will be used.

property.name: dependencies
property.description: The dependencies of this module. Must not be null.

property.name: excludeFolders
property.description: The directories to be excluded. Must not be null.

property.name: generatedSourceFolders
property.description: The directories containing generated the production sources. Must not be null.

property.name: inheritOutputDirs
property.description: If true, output directories for this module will be located below the output directory for the project; otherwise, #outputDir and #testOutputDir will take effect.

property.name: outputDir
property.description: The output directory for production classes. If null, no entry will be created.

property.name: sourceFolders
property.description: The directories containing the production sources. Must not be null.

property.name: testOutputDir
property.description: The output directory for test classes. If null, no entry will be created.

property.name: testSourceFolders
property.description: The directories containing the test sources. Must not be null.
